Fixes and cleanup :
* test complex hierarchy setup/teardown
* cleanup cute_term_depth_[v]printf...
* cleanup internal assertions

Missing features :
* custom mock expectations
* hexdump upon memory content failures
* stack trace upon failures and errors / crashes
* devise API to run a single test ?
* fork isolation ?

JUnit XML support:
* include build flags into generated output:
  * use build flags when gcc invoked with -frecord-gcc-switches
  * these are included withing the .GCC.command.line section of produced Elf and
    may be shown using: readelf -p .GCC.command.line <path_to_elf>
* include build ID into generated output:
  * use build ID when ld invoked with --build-id
  * these are stored into .note.gnu.build-id section of produced Elf and may be
    shown using: readelf -n <path_to_elf>
* include Kconfig build configuration infos into generated output
* all of these might be stored as JUnit XML properties under the top-level
  <testsuite> tagged element or top-level <testsuites> tagged element as shown
  below:
  <testsuites>
      <properties>
          <property name="build-id" value="56deda325eb5fa3b68d11208758e2a63c1b93b25" />
          <property name="build-flags">
            -mabi=aapcs-linux
            -mtune=cortex-a9
            -mcpu=cortex-a9
            -mfpu=neon-vfpv3
            -mfloat-abi=hard
            -mtls-dialect=gnu
            -mno-thumb-interwork
            -marm
            -march=armv7-a+mp+sec+simd
            -auxbase-strip /tmp/ccfCEoY9.ltrans0.ltrans.o
            -ggdb3
            -O2
            -fno-openmp
            -fno-openacc
            -fstack-protector-strong
            -fstack-clash-protection
            -fpie
            -frecord-gcc-switches
            -fvisibility=hidden
            -fuse-linker-plugin
            -fltrans
            /tmp/ccfCEoY9.ltrans0.o
          </property>
          <property name="config">
              CONFIG_MYPROJECT_FEATURE_1=y
              CONFIG_MYPROJECT_FEATURE_2=y
  	    # CONFIG_MYPROJECT_FEATURE_3 is not set
          </property>
     </properties>
     <testsuite ...>
         ...
     </testsuite>
  </testsuites>
